thou their God and father, let thy providence <lb/>
be their portion, thy service their <normalised orig="imployment" auto="true">employment</normalised>, <lb/>
thy Angels their guards; <normalised orig="keepe" auto="true">keep</normalised> them so by <lb/>
thy preventing and restraining grace that they <lb/>
may not by their <normalised orig="owne" auto="true">own</normalised> sins provoke thee to <lb/>
anger and jealousy; and let not the sins of their <lb/>
forefathers be visited upon them in thy anger <lb/>
and displeasure: thou <normalised orig="lovest" auto="true">love</normalised> to <normalised orig="shew" auto="true">show</normalised> mercy, <lb/>
and thou <normalised orig="delightest" auto="true">delight</normalised> in the affections of thy <lb/>
loving <normalised orig="kindnesse" auto="true">kindness</normalised>, and thou art displeased <lb/>
when our <notvariant>vilenesses</notvariant> <normalised orig="constraine" auto="true">constrain</normalised> thee to <normalised orig="powre" auto="true">power</normalised> <lb/>
down thy judgements on us. O be pleased to <lb/>
grant that they living in holy obedience to <lb/>
thee, may feel a <normalised orig="perpetuall" auto="true">perpetual</normalised> <normalised orig="streame" auto="true">stream</normalised> of mercy, <lb/>
refreshing and supporting them, and let them <lb/>
not bear <normalised orig="anothers" auto="true">another</normalised> <normalised orig="burthen" auto="true">burden</normalised>, for thou art just <lb/>
and merciful, righteous and true, and <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> <normalised orig="sentenc'd" auto="true">sentenced</normalised> <lb/>
every one to bear their own iniquity. <lb/>
                  <pb n="96"/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
