the light and life of God to sing praises and <lb/>
                  <pb n="39"/>
                  <lb/>
<normalised orig="eternall" auto="true">eternal</normalised> <normalised orig="hymnes" auto="true">hymns</normalised> to the glory of thy name in <lb/>
eternal ages, though Jesus Christ our Lord. <lb/>
Amen. <lb/>
In whose name let us pray in the words <lb/>
which <normalised orig="himselfe" auto="true">himself</normalised> commanded. saying, <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <quote type="biblical" ana="Mt 6.9-13">OUr Father which art in heaven * Hallowed <lb/>
be thy Name * Thy <normalised orig="Kingdome" auto="true">Kingdom</normalised> come <lb/>
