            <div>
               <head>I.</head>
               <p>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
ALmighty God our glory and our hope, our <lb/>
Lord and Master, the Father of mercy and <lb/>
the God of all comfort, we humbly present to <lb/>
thee the sacrifice of a <normalised orig="thankfull" auto="true">thankful</normalised> spirit in a <normalised orig="joyfull" auto="true">joyful</normalised> <lb/>
acknowledgment of those infinite favours, <lb/>
by which thou <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> supported our state, enriched <lb/>
our spirits, comforted our <normalised orig="sorrowes" auto="true">sorrows</normalised>, <lb/>
<normalised orig="releiv'd" auto="true">relieved</normalised> our necessities, blessed and defended <lb/>
our persons, instructed our ignorances and <lb/>
promoted our <normalised orig="eternall" auto="true">eternal</normalised> interest. We praise <lb/>
thy name for that portion of thy holy word <lb/>
of which thou <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> made us partakers this <lb/>
                  <pb n="40"/>
                  <lb/>
day. Grant that it may bring forth fruit unto <lb/>
thee, and unto <normalised orig="holinesse" auto="true">holiness</normalised> in our whole life, to <lb/>
the glory of thy holy name, the edification of <lb/>
our Brethren, and the <normalised orig="eternall" auto="true">eternal</normalised> comfort of our <lb/>
<normalised orig="soules" auto="true">souls</normalised> in the day of our Lord Jesus. <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
O Almighty and most gracious Father who <lb/>
art the <normalised orig="fountaine" auto="true">fountain</normalised> of life and health and <lb/>
pardon, hear the prayers of thy servants <lb/>
in <normalised orig="behalfe" auto="true">behalf</normalised> of our Brother [or Sister] the miserable <lb/>
for the afflicted, of sinners for him [or <lb/>
her] whom thou <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> smitten. Lord lay no <lb/>
more upon him then thou shalt enable him to <lb/>
<normalised orig="beare" auto="true">bear</normalised>, but give him patience; and <normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised> thou <lb/>
thy <normalised orig="selfe" auto="true">self</normalised> open a door for his escape, even by a <lb/>
holy and reformed life, and a speedy recovery, <lb/>
or else by a blessed death, as thou in thy <lb/>
infinite loving <normalised orig="kindnesse" auto="true">kindness</normalised> shalt choose for thy <lb/>
glory and his <normalised orig="eternall" auto="true">eternal</normalised> interest. <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
O <normalised orig="Eternall" auto="true">Eternal</normalised> and most blessed Saviour Jesus, <lb/>
thou art the bright morning star, and the <lb/>
