eyes with thy beauties, and our hearts with <lb/>
thy comfort and with the <normalised orig="joyes" auto="true">joys</normalised> of God, thou <lb/>
art the <normalised orig="fountaine" auto="true">fountain</normalised> of health and life, of peace <lb/>
and truth, of rest and <normalised orig="holinesse" auto="true">holiness</normalised>; thou <normalised orig="givest" auto="true">give</normalised> to <lb/>
them that want, thou <normalised orig="comfortest" auto="false">comforted</normalised> them that <lb/>
suffer, thou <normalised orig="forgivest" auto="true">forgive</normalised> them that repent, and <lb/>
<normalised orig="hearest" auto="true">hear</normalised> the prayers of all them that call upon <lb/>
thee; we adore thee and praise thy glories, <lb/>
and <normalised orig="rejoyce" auto="true">rejoice</normalised> in thy salvation, and give thee <lb/>
thanks for thy blessing and defending us this <lb/>
night, from all the <normalised orig="evill" auto="true">evil</normalised> which we have deserved <lb/>
every day, and from all the <notvariant>violences</notvariant> and <lb/>
