been restrained by thy <normalised orig="eternall" auto="true">eternal</normalised> <normalised orig="goodnesse" auto="true">goodness</normalised> and <lb/>
thy almighty power. Blessed be God. <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
O Almighty Father of Men and <lb/>
Angels, in whose hands are <lb/>
the <normalised orig="keyes" auto="true">keys</normalised> of life and death, <lb/>
of the womb and of the grave, <lb/>
look down at this time in great <lb/>
mercy and gentlest compassion upon thy servant. <lb/>
Thou <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> O God upon the weakest <lb/>
of mankind fixed the sharpest decree of painful <lb/>
childbirth: but so thou <normalised orig="lovest" auto="true">love</normalised> to <normalised orig="magnifie" auto="true">magnify</normalised> <lb/>
thy mercies and thy power, that thy <lb/>
strength may be seen in our weakness: so let <lb/>
it be O God unto thy handmaid, let thy loving <lb/>
kindness be her confidence and her rest, her <lb/>
hope and her security, now and in the hour of <lb/>
her travail. <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
O Eternal God the Father of <normalised orig="wisedom" auto="true">wisdom</normalised> and <lb/>
