            <div>
               <head>A short <normalised orig="forme" auto="true">form</normalised> of Evening prayer <lb/>
for a family.</head>
               <p>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <head>In the name of our Blessed Lord and <lb/>
Saviour Jesus.</head>
               <p>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <head>Our Father, &amp;c.</head>
               <p>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </div>
            <div>
               <head>The <normalised orig="HYMNE" auto="true">HYMN</normalised>.</head>
               <p>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
O Lord our Lord how excellent is <lb/>
thy Name in all the Earth, thou <lb/>
<normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> set thy glory above the Heavens. <lb/>
When I consider thy heavens, the work <lb/>
of thy fingers, the <normalised orig="moone" auto="true">moon</normalised> and the stars which <lb/>
thou <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> ordained. <lb/>
What is man that thou art <normalised orig="mindfull" auto="true">mindful</normalised> of <lb/>
him, and the Son of man that thou <normalised orig="visitest" auto="true">visited</normalised> <lb/>
him? <lb/>
For thou <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> made him little lower <lb/>
then the Angels, and <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> crowned him with <lb/>
glory and honour. <lb/>
Thou <normalised orig="madest" auto="true">made</normalised> him to have dominion <lb/>
over the <normalised orig="workes" auto="true">works</normalised> of thy hands: and <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> put <lb/>
all things under his feet. <lb/>
All sheep and oxen, yea and the beasts <lb/>
of the <normalised orig="feild" auto="true">field</normalised>, the <normalised orig="fowle" auto="true">foul</normalised> of the <normalised orig="aire" auto="true">air</normalised>, and the fishes <lb/>
of the sea. <lb/>
                  <pb n="58"/>
                  <lb/>
