children; thou didst <normalised orig="blesse" auto="true">bless</normalised> the womb of Elizabeth <lb/>
who was barren; thou <normalised orig="spakest" auto="true">spoke</normalised> the word <lb/>
and the rocks did rend, and they sent forth a <lb/>
pleasant stream: Thy hand is not <normalised orig="shortned" auto="true">shortened</normalised> and <lb/>
thy mercies are not less then ever, no less then <lb/>
infinite, and why should not thy servant hope <lb/>
that thou wilt hear my prayer and grant the <lb/>
desire of my soul: Even so O gracious father <lb/>
let it be as thou <normalised orig="pleasest" auto="true">please</normalised>: thy <normalised orig="wisedom" auto="true">wisdom</normalised> is infinite, <lb/>
and thy counsels are secret, and the <normalised orig="waies" auto="true">ways</normalised> <lb/>
and lines of thy providence are like the path <lb/>
of a bird in the <normalised orig="aire" auto="true">air</normalised>, not to be discovered by <lb/>
our weak sight. <lb/>
