a mighty grace, that she may live a holy life: <lb/>
and be <normalised orig="pleas'd" auto="true">pleased</normalised> to grant this also that those <lb/>
impresses of pious resolutions and religious <lb/>
purposes of fear and love, of hope and desire, <lb/>
which thy grace in the circumstances of her <lb/>
present condition makes upon her, may abide <lb/>
in her soul for ever; and in the <normalised orig="daies" auto="true">days</normalised> of ease <lb/>
and safety may be as operative and productive <lb/>
of holiness, as now they are of a hearty <lb/>
